		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well now you can too solo a rogue up into your mid 30s here is how.&nbsp;&nbsp;First off it is all about the equipment.  As far as wpns goes you have to and I mean have to get Serrated Bone Dirks.  I know on my server they sell for about 3-400pp.  The reason being is that the wpn proc is key.  They proc a spell called engulfing darkness that acts as a snare and a damage over time spell or DoT.  This will do 2 things, add to the dmg output you do and give you a way to run from mobs when you are low on health.  Secondly as far as equipment goes, it is all about the AC.  Get the highest AC items you can.  I recommend if you can to get Jagged bands for your rings they are AC 8 I believe and are well worth it.  Third thing is that you are going to want to get hp items.  The purpose behind this is that they are a rogues healing potions.  When you get low on life and need to run change out to HP items.  They will give you enough life if you get the right ones to get above the one bub area to run faster if needed.  Now as far as location goes always fight near a zone line.  It may sound cheesy but it makes it a lot better when you run and zone instead of loosing those 1-3 blue bubbles of exp.  Also if you are that high of lvl you should be able to make poisons, use em.  Some of the most basic poisons do as much as 250dmg over time.  If you can start off by sneaking up on the mob BS with a poison you stand a good chance of defeating the mob.  But like I said if you have to run you will appreciate the SBDs.  Also learn to bind wound, down time sux.  One last hint to try to find out which mobs that con blue to you have lower HPs.  I can solo a mountain giant at lvl 34 but it has enough HPs that it almost kills me everytime.  The whole point is that you can solo a rogue but it takes the right gear, the right timing, and the right planning.  </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
